name: Honey Wheat Bread II
author: Meghan Monahan
summary: Everybody loves this never fail recipe!  It is lovely served with any meal.
ingredients: 2 cups warm water (110 degrees F/45 degrees C)
directions: Mix in whole wheat flour, salt, and vegetable oil
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface, and knead for at least 10 to 15 minutes
When dough is smooth and elastic, place it in a well oiled bowl
Turn it several times in the bowl to coat the surface of the dough, and cover with a damp cloth
Let rise in a warm place until doubled in bulk, about 45 minutes
Shape into two loaves, and place into two well greased 9 x 5 inch loaf pans
Allow to rise until dough is 1 to 1 1/2 inches above pans
Bake at 375 degrees F (190 degrees C) for 25 to 30 minutes
